==============================================================
SITE: Kitchen Stories
==============================================================

ROLE / CONTEXT
--------------
Role: You are a Senior Web Designer and Food Photographer.
Context: You are building a personal recipe blog called "Kitchen Stories"
for a home cook who wants to share their passion for food with the world.
The site is warm, editorial, and magazine-quality — think Bon Appétit meets
a cozy home kitchen.

PURPOSE
-------
A personal recipe blog featuring curated recipes, a featured dish of the
week, and a personal story about the love of cooking and sharing food.


==============================================================
STEP 2 — BRAND VOICE
==============================================================

Voice archetype: The Warm Host — speaks like a passionate home cook who
has been cooking all day and wants to share every detail with you.

Tone dimensions (scale 1–5):
- Formal ↔ Casual:        2 (casual and warm)
- Serious ↔ Playful:      3 (balanced)
- Reserved ↔ Expressive:  4 (expressive)
- Modern ↔ Timeless:      3 (timeless with modern touches)

Voice rules:
- Speak directly to the reader: "you," "your kitchen," never "customers"
- Food descriptions should be sensory and vivid
- Short sentences. Active voice. Warmth always wins.

Messaging framework:
- Tagline: "Food made with love, shared freely."
- Value prop: "A curated collection of recipes from my kitchen to yours."
- Key phrases: "Every dish tells a story," "From my kitchen to yours,"
  "Cook with love"


==============================================================
STEP 3 — DESIGN SYSTEM
==============================================================

Style keywords: warm, editorial, cozy, magazine, terracotta, cream,
inviting, food photography, artisan

COLOR SYSTEM:
- Primary:      terracotta (#C4623A)
- Secondary:    dark brown (#2C1A0F)
- Accent:       sage green (#7A9E7E)
- Surface-base: cream (#FBF5EC)
- Surface-raised: light tan (#F2E8D8)
- Ink:          mid brown (#6B4C38)

TYPOGRAPHY:
- Display:  Playfair Display (elegant serif with italic variants)
- Body:     Lora (readable serif for recipes and descriptions)
- UI:       DM Sans (clean sans-serif for labels and navigation)

SPACING & LAYOUT:
- Spacing scale (4px base): 4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64, 96, 128
- Container max-width: 1280px
- Grid: 12-col desktop, 8-col tablet, 4-col mobile

MOTION LANGUAGE:
- Easing: cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1)
- Durations: micro 150ms, standard 300ms, expressive 600ms
- Stagger: 100ms between card siblings on scroll-reveal
- Hero: title fade+rise 900ms
- prefers-reduced-motion: collapse all transforms to opacity 200ms


==============================================================
STEP 4 — REFERENCE SCRAPE (for Firecrawl)
==============================================================
Reference URL: https://www.bonappetit.com

Borrow: editorial layout, hero composition, recipe card design, typography
hierarchy, section transitions.
Avoid: any palette or motion choices that conflict with Step 3.


==============================================================
STEP 5 — SECTIONS & LAYOUT (for Stitch)
==============================================================
Section order and goal:

1. Hero        — site name, tagline, 2 CTAs ("Browse Recipes" / "My Story"),
                 full-width editorial image of a beautifully plated dish
2. Recipes     — 3-column recipe card grid with image, category, title,
                 description, difficulty dots, serving size, and cook time
3. Featured    — wide horizontal featured recipe card with large image,
                 title, description, cook time, servings, difficulty
4. Stats Strip — 4 numbers: total recipes, categories, happy cooks, good meals
5. About       — dark background section, image left, personal story right,
                 warm and personal tone
6. Footer      — logo, nav links, copyright

Hero 21st.dev prompt:
  "A warm editorial hero section for a recipe blog with a large serif
  headline, short subtitle, two CTA buttons, split layout with text on
  left and food photography on right, terracotta and cream color palette."


==============================================================
STEP 6 — IMAGERY (use existing images in images/ folder)
==============================================================

Use these existing images — do NOT generate new ones:
- images/hero.jpg      — hero section background
- images/pasta.jpg     — Brown Butter Sage Pasta recipe card
- images/cake.jpg      — Dark Chocolate Layer Cake recipe card
- images/salad.jpg     — Mango Avocado Summer Salad recipe card
- images/featured.jpg  — Slow-Roasted Herbed Lamb Shoulder featured recipe
- images/about.jpg     — About section photo

All images are already optimized and in place. Do not replace them.


==============================================================
STEP 7 — BRAND ASSETS
==============================================================

LOGO brief:
- Concept: elegant wordmark "Kitchen Stories" in Playfair Display
- Style: warm, editorial, no icon needed — typography-driven
- Color: terracotta on cream background

ICON SET (simple, warm, food-themed):
- clock (cook time)
- users (servings)
- star (featured)
- leaf (vegetarian)
- fire (difficulty)


==============================================================
STEP 8 — INTERACTIVE COMPONENTS
==============================================================

Required components:
- Recipe cards with hover lift effect and image zoom
- Featured recipe with meta stats (time, servings, difficulty)
- Smooth scroll navigation
- Sticky navbar with shadow on scroll
- Scroll-triggered fade-in animations on all sections
- Active nav link highlighting on scroll


==============================================================
STEP 9 — ASSEMBLE & ANIMATE (final index.html)
==============================================================

RESPONSIVE BREAKPOINTS: 640 (sm), 1024 (lg), 1280 (xl). Mobile-first.

SEO / META:
- <title>Kitchen Stories — Food made with love, shared freely.</title>
- meta description: A curated collection of recipes from my kitchen to
  yours. From quick weeknight dinners to slow Sunday bakes.
- OG tags: og:title, og:description, og:image, og:type=website

ACCESSIBILITY:
- Landmark regions: header, nav, main, footer
- Alt text on every image
- prefers-reduced-motion honored
- Tap targets 44x44px minimum on mobile

ANIMATION ON ASSEMBLY:
- Hero:           title fade+rise 900ms, staggered words 120ms each
- Section reveals: IntersectionObserver, threshold 0.15, once:true
- Recipe cards:   fade-in with 100ms stagger between cards
- CTA hover:      lift 2px + shadow, 200ms
- Card hover:     lift 8px, image zoom 1.07, box shadow
- Navbar:         box shadow appears after 80px scroll
- Stats strip:    numbers count up on scroll into view
